1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:30,004
okay now I don't know where I suddenly got cut off so I'll just repeat myself on one or two things the important thing is that thinking is developing a mental state and when the Buddha talks about annihilating the thinking he's not talking about annihilating the emotion or the desire that's actually motivating it

2
00:00:30,371 --> 00:00:38,341
In the discourse on how to establish right mindfulness, he asks us to go in there, to feel it and to allow it to exhaust itself.

3
00:00:38,421 --> 00:00:41,505
And that's the process of healing, of course.

4
00:00:44,749 --> 00:00:51,317
Then he says, so this is the more positive, then he gives us a lovely, his usual metaphor.

5
00:00:51,938 --> 00:01:05,858
Just as in the last month of the rainy season, in the autumn, when the crops thicken, a cow herd would guard his cows by constantly tapping and poking them on this side and that, with a stick to check and curb them.

6
00:01:06,438 --> 00:01:07,159
Why is that?

7
00:01:07,599 --> 00:01:14,790
Because he sees that he could be flogged, imprisoned, fined or blamed if he let them stray into the crops.

8
00:01:15,242 --> 00:01:27,239
So too I saw in unwholesome states danger, degradation and defilement, and in wholesome states the blessings of renunciation and the aspect of cleansing.

9
00:01:29,462 --> 00:01:39,917
Now, as I abided thus diligent, ardent and resolute, a thought of renunciation arose in me, and I understood this thought of renunciation has arisen in me.

10
00:01:40,387 --> 00:01:45,915
This does not lead to my affliction, to others' affliction or to the affliction of both.

11
00:01:46,855 --> 00:01:51,442
It aids wisdom, does not cause difficulties and leads to nibbana.

12
00:01:52,123 --> 00:01:57,552
Now here, this is obviously that person who thinks a great deal.

13
00:01:58,733 --> 00:02:09,127
If I think and ponder this thought even for a night, even for a day, even for a night and day, I see nothing to fear from it.

14
00:02:09,901 --> 00:02:15,568
But with excessive thinking and pondering, I might tire my body.

15
00:02:16,468 --> 00:02:20,294
And when the body is tired, the mind becomes strained.

16
00:02:21,175 --> 00:02:25,159
And when the mind becomes strained, it is far from concentration.

17
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:33,050
So I steadied my mind internally, quieted it, brought it to a singleness and concentrated it.

18
00:02:33,531 --> 00:02:34,211
Why is that?

19
00:02:34,752 --> 00:02:37,455
So that my mind should not be strained.

20
00:02:37,776 --> 00:02:39,739
In other words, don't think too much.

21
00:02:40,562 --> 00:02:53,323
So then he goes on, he repeats that with non-ill will, metta, and non-cruelty, compassion.

22
00:02:59,227 --> 00:03:11,001
And then, of course, he repeats this understanding that a bhikkhu who frequently thinks and ponders upon, that will be the inclination of his mind.

23
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:16,407
That will be the inclination of our minds, wherever we continue to think and ponder upon.

24
00:03:16,747 --> 00:03:22,574
But remember, when we're pondering upon things, not to ponder too much, because it strains the mind.

25
00:03:23,795 --> 00:03:28,861
And then, when we're developing the better side of ourselves,

26
00:03:29,264 --> 00:03:56,570
just as in the last month of the hot season when all the crops have been brought inside the villages a cow herd would guard his cows while staying at the root of a tree or out in the open since he needs only to be mindful that the cows are there so too there was need for me only to be mindful that these states were there so in other words once we've established

27
00:03:57,074 --> 00:04:25,291
uh these uh better ways of thinking it's just a matter of keep keep an eye on them that's all and they'll just keep coming the uh the work is letting go of the stuff which uh we don't want because often that's quite delicious and then he says tireless energy was aroused in me and unremitting mindfulness was established my body was tranquil untroubled my mind concentrated and unified

28
00:04:26,081 --> 00:04:33,391
And in this way, he works through the purification and he finally comes upon the moment of awakening.

29
00:04:35,213 --> 00:04:39,319
And this is one of these lovely phrases that you get throughout the scriptures.

30
00:04:40,461 --> 00:04:42,783
He realizes that birth is destroyed.

31
00:04:42,944 --> 00:04:44,346
Becoming is destroyed.

32
00:04:45,427 --> 00:04:47,048
The holy life has been lived.

33
00:04:47,790 --> 00:04:50,553
What had to be done has been done.

34
00:04:50,613 --> 00:04:54,738
There is no more coming back to any state of becoming.

35
00:04:55,629 --> 00:05:18,060
that lovely phrase what had to be done has been done you can imagine the the sense of relief the sense of joy at having finally reached the end of all this of all this stuff this was the third knowledge the first excuse me this was the third true knowledge attained by me in the third watch of the night

36
00:05:18,630 --> 00:05:21,314
Ignorance was banished and true knowledge arose.

37
00:05:21,694 --> 00:05:29,786
Darkness was banished and light arose, as happens in one who abides diligent, ardent and resolute.

38
00:05:30,687 --> 00:05:32,771
This was the third knowledge.

39
00:05:33,132 --> 00:05:39,060
Remember the first two was recollection of all his lives and how he came to this point.

40
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:44,588
And the motivation through all those lives was his moral conduct.

41
00:05:45,360 --> 00:05:54,374
And then he saw beings moving from one place to another, one rebirth to another, driven also by their moral decisions.

42
00:05:54,935 --> 00:06:13,021
So what had been a personal law when he realized that his life was, the movement from life to life, and even in this life, is driven by our ethical decisions, became a universal law when he saw that all beings behave in the same way.

43
00:06:15,331 --> 00:06:22,141
And the third one was the realization that his heart was completely purified of these taints, these defilements.

44
00:06:25,285 --> 00:06:26,245
I've got a bit of time.

45
00:06:26,365 --> 00:06:27,747
I'll go over time a little bit.

46
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:32,595
Suppose because there was a wooded range there.

47
00:06:34,076 --> 00:06:41,827
In a wooded range, there was a great low-lying marsh near which a large herd of deer lived.

48
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:46,072
Then a man appeared desiring their ruin, harm and bondage.

49
00:06:46,773 --> 00:06:50,557
And he closed off the safe and good path that led to their happiness.

50
00:06:51,439 --> 00:07:03,033
And he opened up a false path and he put out a decoy and he set up a dummy so that the large herd of deer might later come upon calamity, disaster and loss.

51
00:07:03,975 --> 00:07:06,499
But another man came desiring their good,

52
00:07:06,697 --> 00:07:35,810
welfare and protection and he reopened the safe and good path that led to their happiness and he closed off the false path and he removed the decoy and destroyed the dummy so that the large herd of deer might later come to growth increase and fulfillment i have given this similarly in order to convey this meaning this is the meaning the great low-lying marsh is a term for sensual pleasure

53
00:07:36,279 --> 00:07:39,403
The large herd of deer is a term for beings.

54
00:07:40,004 --> 00:07:45,473
A man desiring their ruin, harm and bondage is the term for Mara, the evil one.

55
00:07:46,574 --> 00:07:53,624
The false path is a term for the wrong eightfold path, wrong view, wrong intention and so on.

56
00:07:53,644 --> 00:07:57,209
The decoy is a term for delight and lust.

57
00:07:57,228 --> 00:07:59,692
Well, better say indulgence and lust.

58
00:08:00,514 --> 00:08:02,997
The dummy is a term for ignorance.

59
00:08:03,819 --> 00:08:11,553
The man desiring their good and welfare and protection is a term for the targeter, accomplished and fully enlightened.

60
00:08:12,235 --> 00:08:26,942
The safe and good path that led to their happiness is a term for the noble eightfold path, right view, right intention, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness and right concentration.

61
00:08:28,019 --> 00:08:33,086
The safe and good path that leads to happiness has been reopened by me.

62
00:08:33,607 --> 00:08:39,557
The wrong path has been closed off, the dummy removed and the decoy destroyed.

63
00:08:41,419 --> 00:08:56,202
What should be done for his disciples out of compassion by a teacher who seeks their welfare and his compassion for them, who seeks their welfare and has compassion for them, I have done for you.

64
00:08:57,230 --> 00:09:05,903
There are these roots of trees, these empty huts, these meditation centers and corners of bedrooms where you can sit.

65
00:09:06,443 --> 00:09:07,525
Meditate Bhikkhus.

66
00:09:07,985 --> 00:09:10,931
Do not delay or else you will regret it later.

67
00:09:11,731 --> 00:09:13,455
This is my instruction to you.

68
00:09:14,395 --> 00:09:19,744
I don't know about you, but I find this an extraordinarily moving little piece here where he says,

69
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:27,648
What should be done for his disciples out of compassion for a teacher who seeks their welfare and has compassion for them?

70
00:09:28,207 --> 00:09:29,308
I have done for you.

71
00:09:30,250 --> 00:09:34,855
Remember, he spent 45 years, the rest of his life trying to get us out of a mess.

72
00:09:36,235 --> 00:09:42,423
And then he tells us that we must find a place to meditate and do not delay or else you regret it later.

73
00:09:43,043 --> 00:09:44,904
This is our instruction to you.

74
00:09:45,761 --> 00:09:52,293
And what the blessed one said and the big cruiser satisfied and delighted in the blessed one's words.

75
00:09:53,514 --> 00:09:54,155
Very good.

76
00:09:55,116 --> 00:10:00,505
I hope that you've also been inspired by his discourse.

77
00:10:00,525 --> 00:10:03,129
And I think it's time now to do a little sitting.

